episodes.title: Regular Show
episodes.plot: Mordecai the blue jay and Rigby the raccoon play rock paper scissors for a chair, but they get into a 100 times tie.

episodes.title: The Power
episodes.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby need a raise to fix a hole in their bedroom wall, they use a magical keyboard that allows them to do anything they want.

episodes.title: Just Set Up the Chairs
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to prove to Benson that they are not "slackers" by actually completing a job given to them, setting up the chairs for a kid's birthday party.

episodes.title: Caffeinated Coffee Tickets
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try work overtime to earn enough money to buy tickets to a Fist Pump concert, but when they run out of coffee to keep them awake, they enlist the help of a business man and a coffee-bean to keep the coffee flowing.

episodes.title: Death Punchies
episodes.plot: When Rigby becomes tired of losing at "punchies", he visits Death Kwon Do, a mediocre martial-arts clinic, to learn a move that will enable him to win.

episodes.title: Free Cake
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby find a plate that they think would look good with cake, but when they don't have enough money for any, they use Skips' upcoming birthday as an excuse to throw a party and to eat the chocolate cake at the snack bar.

episodes.title: Meat Your Maker
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to look for hot dogs in the meat locker when they burn the ones that Benson bought, but Rigby's incompetence ends up getting them locked in.

episodes.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe
episodes.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby eat Benson's grilled cheese sandwich, Benson makes them buy another one. Unaware that it was Benson's sandwich because of Rigby's lie, Mordecai makes a bet to see who can lie the most without getting caught.

episodes.title: The Unicorns Have Got to Go
episodes.plot: Mordecai buys a special cologne to get the attention of Margaret, but it ends up attracting partying unicorns instead.

episodes.title: Prank Callers
episodes.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby try to prove that they are good prank callers by pranking the "Master Prank Caller", they are inadvertently transported into the 80's.

episodes.title: Don
episodes.plot: Rigby gets jealous of his brother, Don, when he visits the park to stop an audit and is forced to deal with him until he leaves.

episodes.title: Rigby's Body
episodes.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby are told that all the snacks in the snack bar are free for employees, they go on a junk-food spree. But, the next day, when Mordecai cops-out, Rigby continues to eat junk-food, and his body, literally, leaves him.

episodes.title: Mordecai and the Rigbys
episodes.plot: When Mordecai and Rigby make a fake band, they accidentally enter for a live performance, even though they haven't a clue how to play any instruments.
